    "summary": "Alloy exposes one documented HTTP API for onboarding, decisioning, entities, events, and related operations; it accepts either HTTP Basic auth with an Alloy-issued token/secret pair or an OAuth 2.0 client-credentials bearer token derived from that same pair.",
    "description": "Alloy provides identity risk decisioning and onboarding infrastructure for financial institutions and fintechs. Its platform supports entity creation, evaluations, event-driven monitoring, and case-related workflows.",
    "credentials": {
      "alloy_api_keypair": {
        "type": "basic",
        "label": "Alloy account-level API token and secret",
        "generateUrl": "https://developer.alloy.com/public/docs/account-level-api-keys",
        "setup": "In the Alloy dashboard, go to **Roles > Settings > API Keys** and create a new API key. The docs say your role needs permissions to view API keys and create new API keys. Alloy issues a `token` and one or more `secret` values for that key; use them directly for HTTP Basic auth or as the client credentials for OAuth 2.0 client-credentials. See [Account-Level API Keys](https://developer.alloy.com/public/docs/account-level-api-keys) and [Authentication Guide](https://developer.alloy.com/public/docs/authentication-guide)."
      },
      "alloy_oauth_bearer": {
        "type": "oauth2_cc",
        "label": "Alloy OAuth 2.0 bearer token",
        "generateUrl": "https://developer.alloy.com/public/docs/authentication-guide",
        "setup": "First create an Alloy API `token` and `secret` from [Account-Level API Keys](https://developer.alloy.com/public/docs/account-level-api-keys). Then exchange them with the client-credentials flow by POSTing to `https://sandbox.alloy.co/v1/oauth/bearer` with `grant_type=client_credentials` and HTTP Basic auth using `token:secret`. The returned bearer token is valid for one hour and is then sent as `Authorization: Bearer <bearer_token>`. See [Authentication Guide](https://developer.alloy.com/public/docs/authentication-guide)."
      }
    },
